text:
Is she missing her bump already? Cheryl likes pal's pregnancy picture sparking theories she has given birth The singer commented on the post too, responding with the heart eyes emoji Share Cheryl was all heart eyes emoji on her pregnant pal's post Share Get celebs updates directly to your inbox + Subscribe Thank you for subscribing! Could not subscribe, try again later Invalid Email 
It looks like pregnant Cheryl's feeling broody - and has liked a pal's huge bump picture on Instagram. 
The star, who's set to become a first time mum any day now - or already is, depending on the conspiracy theories you may or may not believe - hit Like on friend Anna Hughes-Chamberlain's post. 
The picture showed stylist Anna showing off her large bump with the caption, "Literally carrying a watermelon #hurryupbaby #startingtoscarepeople". 
Cheryl also commented on the picture, using the heart eyes emoji to let her pal know she loved the pic. Video Loading Click to play Tap to play The video will start in 8 Cancel Play now visibly pregnant Cheryl Cole in emotional chat Share this video Cheryl liked the stylist's post, showing her baby bump (Photo: Twitter) Cheryl commented on the post with the heart eyes emoji (Photo: Twitter) Cheryl and her bump (Photo: PA) Cheryl and her boyfriend Liam Payne just being cute (Photo: Getty) Read More What will Liam Payne and Cheryl's baby be called? Couple 'could name child after Simon Cowell' 
Cheryl's yet to officially confirm she's with child, despite making it very clear she was expecting a child as she cradled her bump in a photo campaign for The Prince's Trust and L'Oréal Paris, but until then she'd remained tight-lipped. 
Last week, her boyfriend Liam Payne posted a tweet which could have suggested the baby had already been born. 
Liam, 23, revealed that he was trying his best to stay quiet when getting up early in the morning. 
Was he trying not to wake Cheryl and the little one from their much-needed slumber? 
He posted on Twitter: "Why do I always do the strangest walk when I'm trying to be quiet in a morning". Like us on Facebook
